Second solution: We may parametrize a point in $s$ by any of
$x$, $y$, or $\theta = \tan^{-1} (y/x)$.  Then $A$ and $B$ are
just the integrals of $y\,dx$ and $x\,dy$ over the appropriate
intervals; thus $A+B$ is the integral of $x\,dy - y\,dx$
